easoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 219<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/03 1:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2837.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://forum.insidiousblood.net/images/avatars/badassbuddy_com-dragon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   &quot;Improved Taunt&quot; War only skill</span><hr size=1> Improved Taunt<br>
lvl50+ Warrior only<br>
Cast time: Instant<br>
Reuse: 30 second<br>
Range: 25<br>
Duration: 1 minute<br>
<br>
Effect: <br>
Adds 100 (lvl 50)  to 300 (lvl 65) to hate.<br>
10% slow and 20(lvl 50) to 50(lvl 65) attack debuff. <br>
<br>
<br>
(Note the slow component can be overwritten by stronger slows. Also if a stronger slow is already on mob then the slow component &quot;Will not stick&quot; but the attack debuff and the hate will hit).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I think this is a skill that should be introduced for all up and coming wars and for wars already in the field. Not mind blowing...but it gives the warrior an ability to directly address his lack of taunt ability in the game currently.<br>
<br>
Discuss.<br>
<br>
