<br>
Example-<br>
Monk pulls a mob, paladin does his thing, mob gets in camp slowed and aggro locked on paladin. Mob dies /clap<br>
<br>
Monk pulls to warrior, taunt, and this skill asap aggro should be switched to the warrior and mob is potentially already 10% slowed, making it easier on the cleric for the few seconds untill the mob is slowed by someone better.<br>
<br>
While the paladin example still has aggro locked faster, our skill would enable to seriously reduce the initial chaos we somtimes experience when taunt fails and the slow is resisted and the mob is running at the cleric now cause he had to chain cast SR on the chanter and blahblah. Would be a nice skill while still keeping the aggro dominance to a hybrid. <br>
<br>
This change and our own defensive tables, and the ability to shift fighting stances from tanking to all out damage output for raid stackablity and we'll be golden! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aerildroigheann>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 519<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/03 8:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2837.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &quot;Improved Taunt&quot; War only skill</span><hr size=1> The hate thing is fine, even though it's not needed.  The slow part is utter stupidity.  Even if we were going to get a mana-free slow, why would the recast be less than the duration?  That, among other things, makes absolutely no sense.   Anyway, why do people keep crying about the warrior's taunt ability?  Have you ever even tanked on a raid?  Keeping aggro is not hard unless your entire guild is comprised of lobotomized monkeys.  Yeah, we aren't always the best taunters in exp situations, but who cares then? <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:verdana;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45589" target="top">Aeryl Firebrand</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->,  Overlord<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.freshpope.com/undaunted/" target="top">Undaunted</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, Xegony</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzdaan>azzdaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/03 9:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2837.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &quot;Improved Taunt&quot; War only skill</span><hr size=1> ummm so we are not sitting lfg  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=383773&amp;resize=true" target="top">My Magelo Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rani>rani</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/03 9:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2837.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &quot;Improved Taunt&quot; War only skill</span><hr size=1> Decent idea, although I definately would scratch the slow part doesnt seem fitting at all. <br>
<br>
I am not sure how big the range on normal taunt is, but the range on any new skill as the one you suggest should be slightly higher, to allow it to better be used on incoming mobs.<br>
<br>
I dont like having to waste another hotkey spot for this though, but would of course do it. If they could build this functionality into the normal taunt button, I would prefer it that way. But it is hard to put &quot;burst&quot; quality taunt, on a button that recycles every 6th seconds I guess.<br>
<br>
The good part of your idea of a second hotkey is that it would give us a (small) amount of initial &quot;burst&quot; agro, which would be nice in your everyday exp groups. <br>
<br>
300 hate would not be enough to let a shaman slow on inc I think, but would help a bit on the amount of time they have to wait to avoid agro. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rani>rani</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/29/03 9:54:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=foolsfizzelmore>Fools Fizzelmore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 222<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/03 5:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2837.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://forum.insidiousblood.net/images/avatars/badassbuddy_com-dragon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &quot;Improved Taunt&quot; War only skill</span><hr size=1> Zeb, nice idea....exactly what I was thinking. I would like to make it skill related.<br>
<br>
<br>
I do think that the debuff attached is important though. We know how much these debuffs cause agro. A pure +hate is nice, but with the attached debuff it guarentees real hate...and depending on how verant messes with code in the future, any taunt SHOULD have some debuff attached just to make use of that.<br>
<br>
Aeryl, yes I have tanked raids...I come form one of the top 3 guilds on my server. VT+ guild..so please do not question my tank-ability. As to why put slow on an effect? Why not?<br>
<br>
It is simple...as everyone with a willsaper will tell you....that &quot;snap of the neck&quot; insta agro that the wilsaper gets is excellent. (I do not use it anymore however...I used BoC instead). But the agro from a slow is excellent. Also..think about the &quot;roleplay&quot; aspect...If the improved taunt is some kind of &quot;body blow&quot; to an incomming mob...then an attack debuff and a slow effect is within that domain. A 0 sec stun or a knockback would also be alternatives.<br>
<br>
As to the timer....10 min timer means the skill will be gimped. This needs to be useable every minute or so. A real predicable taunt....this will not put you on top of the hate list..but it will HELP. Also...why is &quot;recast&quot; shorter than duration....easy...ALL spells out there are on a shorter recast than duration. Also...multiple mobs.<br>
<br>
Your average fight in pop (exp mobs) are shorter than 1 min. Depending on group anything from 30 seconds to just over a min or so. So you want a good fast recast. use per min is not overpowered.<br>
<br>
<br>
Finially..I am NOT complaining about warrior taunt. I can work around it just fine. I can get groups all the time no problem. But I think on averge the warrior has been left behind the times. As every other classes gets new spells warriors are slowly slowly slipping behind. We lose our advantages and we are being &quot;nerfed&quot; due to the lack of updates to the warrior skill sets. This is one small step in the right direction.<br>
<br>
